accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research with select materials restricted in accordance with the 2009 donation of the Laurance S. Rockefeller papers. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing audiovisual materials (VHS, audio cassettes) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact a RAC archivist.

When requesting to view audiovisual material, please refer to the Title. Researchers are asked to check the "Restrictions" note for each Title. If a Title does not currently have an access copy, please contact a RAC archivist for further instruction.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Original order, as received. The material was significantly disorganized, originating from closets, cabinets, and other storage areas. To enhance access, this finding aid is arranged into three subgroups:
Within each subgroup, the records are loosely arranged in series by primary subject/topic or property/location as applicable.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The Rockefeller Archive Center has title, copyright, and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them, and has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Laurance S. Rockefeller Office and Home Files are comprised of records received by the Rockefeller Archive Center from several of Laurance S. Rockefeller's homes and residences, primarily including 834 Fifth Avenue in New York City, and Kent House in Pocantico Hills, NY. Select files were also received from other properities such as Woodstock, VT; Hawaii; and the U.S. Virgin Islands.

The collection also contains a variety of files created and maintained by the staff of the Rockefeller family office, Room 5600, Rockefeller Center, New York City, many of which may have been brought home, or transported back and forth to a residence by either Laurance S. or Mary French Rockefeller or their staff.

Files document: LSR and Rockefeller family correspondence and activities; LSR biographical materials, awards, and speeches; art and estate files; a variety of Mary French Rockefeller and Laurance S. Rockefeller personal and philanthropic interests such as: LSR Fund, MSKCC, and YWCA; as well as meomrial serivce files.
Properties documented primarily include those in: New York City; Pocantico Hills; Woodstock, VT; Wyoming; the Virgin Islands and Rockresorts.
